dismissalText.commentary: James Faulkner c Powell b Sammy 39 (67b 3x4 0x6 88m) SR: 58.2

dismissalComment.html: caught at deep midwicket! So there is the wicket, they had to wait almost 20 overs for it. Faulkner makes room by moving outside leg and tries to flat-bat that to the stands at deep midwicket but it goes high, and is caught just inside the boundary by Powell, who didn't have to move much at all

headshotImage.caption: Phillip Hughes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Phillip Hughes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: caught at midwicket! Oh no! There goes another one to a shot he would have thought was going towards the boundary. It was a hit-me delivery, short of length on the body, and Hughes goes for a pull. He had all the time at Sammy's pace, but he neither places it on the ground, or high up in the air, hits it straight to Darren Bravo at midwicket.

dismissalText.commentary: Usman Khawaja c Powell b Roach 3 (14b 0x4 0x6 16m) SR: 21.42

dismissalComment.html: caught at square leg! Oh wow! That is a double-handed ripper. It was a length ball on the middle stump and Khawaja went for a flick, he timed it really well and I thought it was heading towards the boundary, but Powell at square-leg dives full length to his right, catches the ball while in air and cuts off Uzzie's innings.

dismissalText.commentary: Aaron Finch c DM Bravo b Holder 11 (22b 2x4 0x6 29m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: caught at cover! One handed! Another catch plucked from nowhere. Finch went back to the short of length delivery outside off and smashed it, reallly smashed it. The only thing was that he hit in the air, and Bravo pulls off a super reflex catch. he went with two hands, but only could get a hand on it as it went too quick to him

dismissalText.commentary: Kieran Powell lbw b Starc 83 (90b 10x4 2x6 133m) SR: 92.22

dismissalComment.html: another yorker, this time on the off and middle stump, Powell digs it out and Mitchell Starc catches it in return. Australians appeal for lbw as the ball might have hit the pad before the bat. the umpire says not out and they ask for a review. It hits the pads first..and it was going to hit off and middle. Starc takes out Powell.

dismissalText.commentary: Dwayne Bravo c Wade b Maxwell 45 (56b 4x4 2x6 83m) SR: 80.35

dismissalComment.html: Maxwell gets a wicket!! It was a flatter delivery from round the wicket and Bravo went for a cute little late cut and ended up edging it to the keeper. Leaves straight away, Maxwell roars..

that's it! It's all over, Gayle talks to Powell and thinks about a review, Powell says no chance. It was full and swinging away, it pitched around off and Gayle was hit right in front as he got squared-up a bit. Starc strikes in his first over..

headshotImage.caption: Ramnaresh Sarwan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ramnaresh Sarwan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: it is a gonner! He thought that the over had finished, but it hadn't. The ball is a perfect left-armer's delivery, pitches on length on the middle stump line, and curves back in. Sarwan had taken a step forward but wasn't able to take his foot out of the way, stuck in front and he was dead the moment he missed it..

and the nostalgic picture is torn apart by a full delivery from Starc! He had been bowling a slightly shorter length this over, and now he pushes it full and on the stumps and Lara is late to bring his bat down, that was hitting middle of middle. Bravo reviews in hope, but that was out even to a blind eye...

dismissalComment.html: gets a short ball on off stump which goes past the outside edge as the batsman tries to sway away.. Everyone goes up on an appeal for caught behind. the umpire shakes his head, but they call for a review.. A brute of a delivery.. Hot-spot being tested. Was there some glove on it? Not sure...hot-spot not very conclusive.. They are checking for sound cues... too long being taken here (we are into the zone where DRS starts becoming a bit of a pain).. He gives him out.. on the sound cue.. Well, I thought ..Speechless I am..

dismissalText.commentary: Jason Holder run out (Bailey/Maxwell) 9 (28b 1x4 0x6 31m) SR: 32.14

commentTextItems.html: comes out of the pitch and drives it straight to cover. There is hesitation between the batsmen though and that costs Holder his wicket as he is inches short of the crease at the non-striker's end..

commentPostTextItems.html: It has all ended in a bit of a haste really. The match was nicely set up by a counter-attacking stand between Powell and Dwayne Bravo - both getting half-centuries - but once Bravo was out, it opened the floodgates and the innings folded quickly. Mitchell Starc was superb again - he has two five-fors from two games now - and he was the destructor-in-chief today. The questionable application of DRS left a bit of sour taste, but then apart from two, none of West Indies' batsmen applied themselves. Australia take a 2-0 lead in the ODI series, but given the match today, the series could get closer.

George Bailey is the man of the match. Not much of a presentation ceremony here, so we can't bring the comments from the captains. But there will be stories out later from press-conferences and I for one would like to read more about the decision-making process. It's the end of our coverage here and Brydon's report is being updated. Thanks for all your comments and feedback. This is Devashish Fuloria signing off from here.. ciao ciao.
Phil: "Sorry, but totally irresponsible play by Narine. Blocking out the last two balls of the over would have sufficed... but ah no; gotta go for glory!"

gav: "This game has had everything so far; brilliant fielding from the West Indies, a smashing century from Bailey, Powell out-hitting Bravo and Pollard, a shocking DRS call, Narine hitting 4 sixes in row, and now Wade has effected a stumping!! I don't know what to believe."

commentTextItems.html: fuller delivery on the off and middle, driven on the up to mid-off
comes up with the slower bouncer, but it goes over the batsman's head. Mitchell Johnson not very happy with the call.
makes room and swats a short of length delivery to midwicket with the toe-end of his bat
short ball down the leg side, everyone appeals for something, but it was way down the leg side
moves way outside leg, Johnson follows him with a short ball, Holder flat bats it to mid-on
another shot that highlights Holder's potential. He drives this full ball beautifully but hits the stumps at the non-striker's end
length ball on off stump, Holder comes forward to defend, inside edges the ball to his pads

commentPreTextItems.html: Four in four...can we have more?

flatter delivery, makes do difference. He comes out and picks the ball of a length and goes over a leaping long-off fielder..
no. 3, to the same area as the previous one. Flighted, he charges down and smacks it over long-off
and another one, this one into the crowd beyond long-off
straight to the sight screen as Narine makes room and slogs it over the bowler's head for his first six
moves outside leg and Mitchell follows him with the short one, Holder goes for a pull but doesn't connect

back of length on the middle stump, defended back to the bowler

commentPreTextItems.html: Karthik: "Blaming the DRS for Thomas' decision is silly. The ICC clearly states that decisions can be overturned on conclusive evidence. Asad Rauf is the one to be blamed for ruling him out when there was not anything clear on hot spot."

dismissalComment.html: another yorker, this time on the off and middle stump, Powell digs it out and Mitchell Starc catches it in return. Australians appeal for lbw as the ball might have hit the pad before the bat. the umpire says not out and they ask for a review. It hits the pads first..and it was going to hit off and middle. Starc takes out Powell.

dismissalComment.html: it is a gonner! He thought that the over had finished, but it hadn't. The ball is a perfect left-armer's delivery, pitches on length on the middle stump line, and curves back in. Sarwan had taken a step forward but wasn't able to take his foot out of the way, stuck in front and he was dead the moment he missed it..

dismissalText.commentary: Darren Bravo lbw b Starc 14 (20b 3x4 0x6 26m) SR: 70

dismissalComment.html: and the nostalgic picture is torn apart by a full delivery from Starc! He had been bowling a slightly shorter length this over, and now he pushes it full and on the stumps and Lara is late to bring his bat down, that was hitting middle of middle. Bravo reviews in hope, but that was out even to a blind eye...

dismissalText.commentary: Devon Thomas c Wade b Starc 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: gets a short ball on off stump which goes past the outside edge as the batsman tries to sway away.. Everyone goes up on an appeal for caught behind. the umpire shakes his head, but they call for a review.. A brute of a delivery.. Hot-spot being tested. Was there some glove on it? Not sure...hot-spot not very conclusive.. They are checking for sound cues... too long being taken here (we are into the zone where DRS starts becoming a bit of a pain).. He gives him out.. on the sound cue.. Well, I thought ..Speechless I am..

dismissalText.commentary: Daren Sammy c Faulkner b Maxwell 8 (16b 1x4 0x6 20m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: caught at long off! boom! He was not to the pitch of the delivery, but he went for the big shot nonetheless, and just scoops it over to the fielder at long-off. And just like that, Maxwell has three. What a day for him!

dismissalText.commentary: Jason Holder run out (Bailey/Maxwell) 9 (28b 1x4 0x6 31m) SR: 32.14

dismissalComment.html: comes out of the pitch and drives it straight to cover. There is hesitation between the batsmen though and that costs Holder his wicket as he is inches short of the crease at the non-striker's end..
